1. Encapsulation
    The process of binding states and behaviour together is called as an encapsulation.
    we can achieve encapsulaiton with help of class
    In encapsulation helper method plays the major role.
    Helper methods: 
        Two types -> getter method & setter method
          getter method is used to get the data
          setter method is used to set the data

    All the variables are in private accesser modifier
    using public setter method used to set the data & public getter method used to get the data.

    class Encapsulaiton_Ex {
      private int id;
      private String name;

      //setter method
      public static void setId(int id){
        this.id = id;
      }
      public static void setName(String name){
        this.name = name;
      }

      //getter method
      public static int getId(){
        return id;
      }
      public static String getName(){
        return name;
      }
    }

2. Polymorphism
      The process of bin
      There are two types of polymorphism
        i. Compile time polymorphism
        ii. Run time polymorphism

      i). Compile Time polymorphism
          There are 4types of compile type polymorphism
          They are:     
              * Method Overloading --> A class having same method name but different formual arguments.
              * Constructor Overloading --> A class having same constructor name but different formual arguments.
              * Method Shadowing --> A parent class & child class having the same static method signature.
              * Variable Shadowing --> A parent class & child class having the same variable name.

      2). Run time polymorphismn
          There are only in run time polymorphism
          That is Method OVerriding
          Method Overriding:
              The parent & child class having the same method signature is called as an method overriding
              Note: non static method only


